OBJECTIVE:

4.a To find the largest from a series

•	Read the count of the series (N) from memory location 4600H and store it in R1 register. 
•	Find the largest among the ‘N’ series of numbers starting from memory location 4601H and store the result in register R2.


ALGORITHM

1.	Start
2.	Initialize DPTR = 4600
3.	Read the number of data (N) to be transferred from memory location 4600H and store it in R1 register 
4.	Decrement R1 register
5.	Increment DPTR
6.	Read the first number and store it in the R2 register
7.	Increment DPTR
8.	Read the next number and store it in the accumulator and R3 register
9.	Compare the numbers by subtracting R2 from the accumulator and store the result in the accumulator 
10.	If the carry flag is set, move the content of R3 to the R2 register
11.	Decrement the R1 register and if it is not equal to zero go to step 5 else go to step 12
12.	Initialize DPTR = 4700
13.	Store the largest number in R3 register to the memory location 4700
14.	Stop

